{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ῥῆγ-μα</b>, ατος, τό, <br /> (ῥήγνυμι) <b>breakage, fracture</b>, joined with σπάσμα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Aër.” 4,compare 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.198, 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 3.74\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; with στρέμμα (a strain), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 2.21, 11.14. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>laceration, rupture</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 10.160, 18(2).882, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 635a4. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>rent, tear</b>, in clothes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Archippus Comicus 38. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>cleft, chasm</b>, ῥ. τῆς γῆς [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 628b29 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>chink</b>, ἐν τοίχοις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 13.6.8 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; <b>breach</b> in a dyke, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PLond.” 1.131r. 45, 60 (1st c.AD). \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>lesion</b> or <b>rupture</b> of tissue, ὅταν ὑπὸ βίης διαστέωσιν αἱ σάρκες ἀπ᾽ ἀλλήλων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ φυσῶν” 11, compare 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 1.238, 10.232; especially oflung, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ τόπων τῶν κατὰ ἄνθρωπον” 14, “Morb.” 1.20 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:hence <b>ῥηγμᾰτίας</b>, ου, ὁ, <b>one who has such a rupture</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. author] “Aër.” 4, 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 3.146, 4.10; τοὺς ἐκ βηχὸς ῥηγματίας “Hippiatrica” 22 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; but ῥηγματίας πλεύμονος perhaps = <b>pleurisy</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ νούσων” 2.53 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>ῥηγμᾰτώδης</b>, ες, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Epid.” 7.26. \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G4485","accentedUnicode":"ῥῆγμα","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G4486","matchingForm":"ῥήγνυμι","stepTransliteration":"rēgnumi","gloss":"to throw violently","_zh_tw_Gloss":"裂開","_es_Gloss":"tirar violentamente","_zh_Gloss":"裂开"}],"shortDef":"destruction, ruin","mediumDef":"destruction, ruin <br /><b>a rent; a crash, ruin,</b> <ref='Luk.6.49'>Lk. 6:49</ref>*","stepGloss":"destruction","stepTransliteration":"rēgma","count":1,"_es_Definition":"ruina, destrucción","_zh_tw_Definition":"傾毀,倒塌(路 6:49)","_zh_Definition":"倾毁,倒塌(路 6:49)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"sự phá huỷ.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"破壞","_es_Gloss":"destrucción","_zh_Gloss":"破坏"}]}